BtServiceRequest * BtConnectionlessController::CleanUpRequestExecution (  BtResultCode  result_code,
BtRequestType  request_type
)  [protected]
 

Finalize the execution of an currently executing request.

When a request is submitted to the Bluetooth stack for execution, the Bluetooth stack function can return FALSE, if the request is rejected by the Bluetooth stack, or the appropriate callback function is called to report the state of the ongoing request. In all of these cases CleanUpRequestExecution should be called.
CleanUpRequestExecution determines on the passed in parameters whether the member variable m_executing_request should be cleared or not. When CleanUpRequestExecution resets m_executing_request to 0, the id of the cleared request is returned.

Parameters:
result_code A BtResultCode containing the result of the execution of the currently ongoing request.
request_type A BtRequestType containing the kind of request for which the result code is passed in.
Returns:
((UINT32)(-1)) Depending on result_code and request_type the function decided not to resest m_executing_request to 0.
Any other UINT32 m_executing_request is set to 0 and the id of the finalized request is returned.

btapi_cb_funp_t * BtConnectionlessController::GetCallbackFunctionPointers (   )  const [protected, virtual]
 

Return a pointer to the structure of function pointers for the callbacks.

When the APOXI Bluetooth is registered at the stack an unique user id is generated. This user id identifies the storage of a structure containing all possible callback function addresses. The storage is allocated by the Bluetooth stack and a pointer to this storate is returned at registration. This pointer is stored in the member variable m_callback_functions.
GetCallbackFunctionPointers enables the access to this member variable.

Returns:
A pointer to a btapi_cb_funp_f, which is a structure containing all the function pointers for all callback functions that are needed by the Bluetooth stack.

Implements BtController.

BtServiceRequest * BtConnectionlessController::GetExecutingRequest (   )  const [protected]
 

Return currently executing request.

The execution of requests within the controller is limited to one request at a time. A pointer to the currently running request is stored in the member variable m_executing_request. This member variable is used to save informations about the request during its execution in the Bluetooth stack and to enable the assignment between the callback function calls and the request.

Returns:
A pointer to a BtRequest containing the currently running request or 0, if no reqeust is currently running.

UINT8 BtConnectionlessController::GetPriority (   )  const [virtual]
 

Return the startup priority for this controller.

GetPriority is needed to determine the startup sequence of the various constrollers by which the subsystem manager starts them.
The value 0xFF means that it is the most important controller and should be started first. The value 0x00 denotes the least important controller, that will be started at the end of the controller startup sequence.

Returns:
An UINT8 containing the priority of this controller that describes the point of time in the startup sequence, when to start it.

Reimplemented from SubSystem.

btapi_userid_t BtConnectionlessController::GetUserId (   )  const [protected, virtual]
 

Return the user id of this contoller assigned to by the Bluetooth stack.

When the APOXI Bluetooth is registered at the Bluetooth stack an unique id is generated and returned by the Bluetooth stack. This id has to be used at each API call to let the Bluetooth stack determine which set of callback function pointers to use for the invocation of a notification callback.
The user id generated by the Bluetooth stack is for internal use only and so the application programme needs no possibility to access this id.

Returns:
A btapi_userid_t containing the user id assigned by the Bluetooth stack.

Implements BtController.

BOOLEAN BtConnectionlessController::PrepareRequestExecution (  BtServiceRequest *  request  )  [protected]
 

Perpare the execution of a submitted request.

When a request is submitted to the controller for execution PrepareRequestExecution checks if an other request is currently running. If so the function returns FALSE, otherwise the member variable m_executing_request is set to point to the passed in request and TRUE is returned.

Parameters:
request A pointer to a BtRequest, that should be exectuted.
Returns:
TRUE The passed in request can be executed.
FALSE There is an other request currently running, so the passed in request can not be executed.
